Build ID: I20070625-1500

Steps To Reproduce:
1. Install Eclipse 3.3, EMF 2.3, ATL 2.0.0rc2
2. Run the following skeleton code:

import ... ;

EMFModelLoader ml;
AtlModelHandler amh = AtlModelHandler.getDefault("EMF");

ASMEMFModel metaModel = (ASMEMFModel)((AtlEMFModelHandler)amh).loadModel(String metaid, amh.getMof(), new FileInputStream(String metapath));

ByteArrayOutputStream outModel = new ByteArrayOutputStream();
ASMEMFModel OUT = ASMEMFModel.newASMEMFModel("OUT", "OUT", metaModel, ml);
OUT.setCheckSameModel(false);

AtlLauncher myLauncher = AtlLauncher.getDefault();
myLauncher.launch(URL trans, HashMap<String, URL>libs, HashMap<String, ASMEMFModel>models_including_OUT, Collections.EMPTY_MAP, Collections.EMPTY_LIST, Collections.EMPTY_MAP);

amh.saveModel(OUT, outModel); // crashline

This results in:

java.lang.NullPointerException
at org.eclipse.m2m.atl.engine.AtlEMFModelHandler.saveModel(AtlEMFModelHandler.java:144)
at org.eclipse.m2m.atl.engine.AtlEMFModelHandler.saveModel(AtlEMFModelHandler.java:65)
at crashline




More information:
Replacing the second string "OUT" in the call to saveModel by an empty string or null doesn't help.
